VALIDATION STATUS
=================

Each claim has a status: PROVEN, DEMONSTRATED, or PROJECTED.

    PROVEN = formally verified in Lean 4, or mathematically
             derived with no empirical assumptions.

    DEMONSTRATED = reproduced in simulation (FDTD/C engine)
                   with measurable results.

    PROJECTED = follows logically from proven/demonstrated
                claims but not yet independently tested.


T — Substrate:

    T enables distinction.                              PROVEN
    (Lean 4: evolution_creates_distinction,
     no_change_no_distinction.)

    T flows forward (monotonic).                        PROVEN
    (Lean 4: t_advances, no_backward.)

    T is not a spatial dimension.                       PROVEN
    (Lean 4: spatial_independent_of_t —
     pathTransmit does not take T as input.)

    Laws are T-invariant.                               PROVEN
    (Lean 4: laws_t_invariant, walls_t_invariant.)


Layer 0 — Distinction:

    {2} as basis of computation.                        PROVEN
    (Lean 4: all boolean operations derived from binary.)


Layer 1 — Position:

    Position determines meaning (spatial vs flat).      DEMONSTRATED
    (+98% improvement, ONETWO v5, Test F.)

    3D spatial addressing: 268M positions.              PROVEN
    (Lean 4: spec_spatial_positions, native_decide.)


Layer 2 — Collision:

    (A+B)² = A² + 2AB + B².                            PROVEN
    (Lean 4: collision_energy theorem.)

    (A+B+C)² = A²+B²+C² + 2AB+2AC+2BC.                PROVEN
    (Lean 4: collision3_energy theorem.)

    Superlinearity: collision > sum of parts.           PROVEN
    (Lean 4: superlinear, superlinear3.)

    Cross-term extracts product: r = 1.0000.            DEMONSTRATED
    (Collision protocol, amplitude sweep.)

    Dot product from collision: r = 0.9997.             DEMONSTRATED
    (Collision protocol, cross-term extraction.)

    Collision energy deterministic: std = 0.00.          DEMONSTRATED
    (10 trials, identical results.)


Layer 3 — Impedance:

